4. The Supervisor-Led Routing System

The Supervisor node serves as the "Command and Control" center. It is not a separate agent but a collection of conditional edges within LangGraph that interpret the global state to orchestrate flows.

Command Pattern Implementation

The Supervisor utilizes the Command(goto=..., update={...}) pattern. This allows the system to route to the next specialist agent and update the global state in a single atomic operation. By combining the route and update steps, we reduce computational overhead and ensure the state reflects the current agent's output before the next node executes.

Belt-and-Suspenders Safety

To prevent infinite loops and runaway token consumption, the Supervisor enforces a strict agent_call_count tracker. The MAX_AGENT_CALLS is set to 6. If this threshold is hit, the graph forces a FINISH state. The Supervisor determines this by reading the current state—original request, extracted entities, and cumulative agent results—to verify if the user's intent is satisfied.


